WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.880
The thing that's made rstudio, and now Posit, so amazing is the community.

00:00:06.880 --> 00:00:12.000
We love and value our Open Source community, and we're so appreciative of everyone who

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:15.040
has helped make Posit what it is today.

00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:16.959
And our community is you.

00:00:16.959 --> 00:00:22.340
You live and work on every continent, and one of the most used datasets for teaching

00:00:22.340 --> 00:00:23.340
is even from Antarctica.

00:00:24.340 --> 00:00:30.700
You use R for school, or work, or fun, answering questions that are important to you.

00:00:30.700 --> 00:00:36.700
You work on projects in education, science, marketing, public health, government, economics,

00:00:36.700 --> 00:00:41.540
finance, libraries, astronomy, and so, so much more.

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:45.720
You create and share thousands of resources to help others.

00:00:45.720 --> 00:00:50.779
You contribute to code and documentation on hundreds of Open Source projects.

00:00:50.779 --> 00:00:55.619
You're involved in the community, sharing with each other in your organizations and

00:00:55.619 --> 00:00:58.139
in user groups around the world.

00:00:58.139 --> 00:01:01.740
And of course, you write millions of lines of code.

00:01:01.740 --> 00:01:06.739
Thanks to you, R is one of today's top 10 programming languages.

00:01:06.739 --> 00:01:12.540
I've been using R for almost 20 years now, and the transformation of the language and

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:15.779
the community just blows my mind.

00:01:15.779 --> 00:01:21.580
I'm so awed and grateful for all that we have built together, and I, and everyone at

00:01:21.580 --> 00:01:23.779
Posit, wishes you all the best for the coming year.

